## Usage

Register the module with the kernel during startup:

```go
import (
    "context"

    "github.com/fzihak/aethercore/sdk"
    mod "github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/{{.ModuleName}}"
)

func main() {
    registry := sdk.NewModuleRegistry()
    mc := sdk.NewModuleContext("{{.ModuleName}}")

    if err := sdk.StartModule(context.Background(), registry, mod.New(), mc); err != nil {
        panic(err)
    }
    // ... run your application
    _ = sdk.StopAll(context.Background(), registry)
}
```

## Capabilities

This module currently requests **no** kernel capabilities.
Add entries to the `Capabilities` field in `Manifest()` as needed:

| Constant            | Permission                         |
|---------------------|------------------------------------|
| `sdk.CapNetwork`    | Outbound TCP/UDP connections       |
| `sdk.CapFilesystem` | Read/write access to the local FS  |
| `sdk.CapState`      | Persistent state via the kernel DB |
| `sdk.CapMesh`       | Participation in the agent mesh    |

